text:
Having been to several AF outlets, AF Pasir Panjang is one of the best.

The gym is spacious, well-lit and well equipped. For those who love spinning, you can also find an abundance of spin bikes and classes here.

Huge emphasis is placed on hygiene and cleanliness, with twice a day cleaning (2-3am & 2-3pm). Washroom and showering facilities are clean and well maintained.

Staff are all friendly and approachable (especially club manager William).

Highly recommend everyone to check out this place!

author: Sihan Goi
text:
Large and spacious, with separate spaces for free weights/plate loaded machines, other weight machines/cardio equipment, and a large room for group classes. The shower area is one of the better ones for AF too. Also, I like the fact that upgrades have been made over the years. Currently, there are 4 power racks, 2 back to back half racks, 2 lifting platforms, multiple adjustable benches, weight plates/bumper plates, multiple Olympic barbells (Ziva and Hammer Strength ones that spin, and a few old ones), hex bars, EZ bars, and heavier dumbells up to 47.5kg. Many of these are quite new. There's also a C2 rower, water rower, assault bike, and many spin bikes. I can't list all the equipment, just look at my pictures. There were a few things previously preventing it from getting 5 stars IMHO, but they've all been addressed one by one over the years, so it gets 5 stars from me now. The only bad things I can think of is the fact that you need to be relatively quiet while lifting. I've gotten complained before a couple years ago while setting the barbell down a bit too loudly, but bumper plates and platforms would kinda address this. Also, some of the staff aren't very familiar with the equipment when I had some questions. Other than that, it's awesome!

Update: I had to drop this to 4 stars, because despite the platform, bumper plates, and new hammer strength Olympic spin bars, you apparently can't do Olympic weightlifting here. I got complained by staff for dumping the bar from overhead, despite all the equipment being designed specifically to be dumped from overhead, because it was "too loud". There's no point getting the best equipment in the world if you can't use them the way they were designed to be used.

Arguably the best AF in Singapore.

For starters, this AF is massive, and that means plenty of weights, machines, cardio and workout areas. This means that you no longer have to keep hovering around power racks waiting for the next guy to finish his sets.

General upkeep of the place is good, with minor wear as expected of any commercial gym. Locker and restroom facilities are basic but good (can't expect Pure Fitness facilities, and that's not what most gym goers are looking for).

Accessibility is excellent, about a 5 minute walk from Pasir Panjang MRT.

All in all, I'm impressed enough with this gym that I'm seriously considering making this my regular gym even though it is slightly out of the way for me.

text:
I joined Anytime Fitness a few months ago and it has been great so far. The front desk staff at the Pasir Panjang outlet is really helpful and friendly. They have also assisted with requests when needed. The outlet is very spacious and well maintained with a good number of machines and free weights. The gym also has a positive and friendly vibe that encourages ones to work out regularly. While many corporate gyms in Singapore have hiked up their prices in recent years (and continue to increase), the membership rates at Anytime Fitness remain affordable and fixed.

Moreover, many corporate gyms close early on weekends or closed on public holidays and it becomes very inconvenient to get a proper workout. The 24/7 access at Anytime Fitness gives members the flexibility and ease to work out when their schedule permits. I would definitely recommend joining this gym.

text:
I had a fantastic experience at Anytime Fitness Pasir Panjang! The gym is spacious, clean, and well-equipped, with friendly and helpful staff who create a welcoming environment.

My main goal was to lose belly fat and improve general fitness, and I‚Äôm thrilled with the results. Thanks to Shahrizan, my personal trainer, I lost 5.5kg during the training period (mid July- mid Nov 2024) and achieved a transformative change in how I feel. Shah assessed my fitness level thoroughly and designed a customized program tailored to my needs. He also guided me with a sustainable diet routine, ensuring the journey was effective and manageable.

The training was not just about the results but also about sustainability and long-term fitness habits. I highly recommend Anytime Fitness Pasir Panjang and Shah for anyone looking to embark on their fitness journey.

text: Amazing place great environment friendly people!!

author: demoncursekwan K

author: Mohd Asrih
text: Gym is spacious. Staff is friendly and helpful.

author: Andri Kristian
text: Spacious gym, with v good equipment and facilities and good staffs

author: Sam Clingan
text: Great gym and facilities. Highly recommended!

author: Ëæ∞ËÄÅ
text: The staff is very friendly, the gym is very large, well-equipped, clean and comfortable

author: manfred goh
text: Is a good and clean outlet which I always visit! Thumb up to the staff and team!

author: Joaquin Beniga
text: The staff very good mammerd and accommodating Jemmy and Ian so great attitude as well

author: Tabasco Guzzler
text: Super spacious gym that allows users to work out comfortably. There are 3 separate areas - each section is large, with high ceilings & well-spaced equipment. Interesting range of cardio machines, some of which I had never seen before e.g. the lateral trainer that conditions your body in an unconventional way. Some machines need maintenance. Bathrooms are gender-separate & the largest of all the AF gyms I‚Äôve tried. Usually clean, but there was a pungent pee smell in the ladies‚Äô loo last week. Counter staff could be friendlier.

author: haris ismail
text:
Big spacious gym. Very well maintained equipment and also clean. Love the wide arrays of Olympic bars and trap bar.

Even have air bike and a spacious area to do warm-ups and cool down. The restroom are spacious too as they have separated males and females.

author: Alex Liu
text: Very spacious, complete set of equipments, friendly and helpful staff. Perfect for a workout before or after work.

author: Sarbjit Singh
text:
One of the best gyms I have been to. A variety of equipment. Additional benches and multiple racks with dedicated weights for different equipment, don't need to grab weights from other machines.

There is also ample spaces between equipment. Great studio space for post workout cardio or abs.

Staff are great and friendly. Even if you are not on a arrangement with them for training, they will assist out of courtesy. Very different from other gym, staff does not give a glance even if you are doing the workouts all wrong.

Like the crowd here, those who are focused on getting a workout done the moment they step in.

A big huge gym just along the road, not nestled into some shopping mall or  building.

author: Damon Wong
text:
Love the ground floor gym with huge space. Feels exclusive yet accessible at the same time. Not easy to find places like these anymore.

Had a good workout with the well maintained equipment, shower has bench to put your stuff too.

Well managed AF by Tiffany, and good chat with Bastien too!

author: Jon Ho
text: one of the best anytimes in Singapore. the staff are super warm and welcoming, and they‚Äôre always trying to make your gym experience just a little more enjoyable and fulfilling without it being too intrusive.

author: yanty jantan
text: A home club member here since Day 1 and my its my go-to gym because I like the huge space, ample shower facilities for ladies and not too crowded during weekends. Plenty of gym machines here for workout because they brought in new ones a few months ago. I had been training under PT Shah at this gym and I must say I am deeply thankful for all the guidance he had given for the past 2 yrs - I have learnt so much during the sessions with him. Despite the serious face, he is friendly, patient and a good listener. He really knows how to tweak my workouts when I was recovering from back aches & a frozen shoulder so I could continue to exercise safely . Highly recommend him if you are looking for a dedicated PT and need that extra push!

author: isaiah
text: Staff was very helpful. Love the set up of squat racks and barbells

author: Washeem Mohamed
text:
Have been going to AF PP for almost a year and its been a pleasant experience thus far. A very well maintained place with an extremely large floor space and a good number of equipment! With almost 4 squat racks it allows me to complete workouts without having to wait for machines to be available.
Staff are also extremely kind and helpful.
I can also check their Instagram to see how crowded the gym is making my trips super efficient!!

author: candy t
text: Very friendly staff and spacious gym, good atmosphere all around. Been to a few outlets and this is the best by far! It's nice to see friendly faces in the evenings after getting off work and the gym provides a stress-free environment to work out. Appreciate that it has some classes as well as an added bonus!

author: Kay
text:
The gym is really spacious. There are about 6 racks for us to usr for squats and bench presses. The gym has large number of machines so that it can serve many members at any given time, especially during peak hours. Gym is clean. Shower area is aircon, and has number of shower cubicles within the gym. It will be very helpful for the ones who workout in the morning and the head to work. Gym is well maintained.

Update: with new renovation, AF Pasir panjang is even better now. Serves free coffee too! Perhaps my favourite gym in Singapore.

author: Kaiyan Hou
text: Been here for half a year, one of the best AF outlets in Singapore on my personal recommendation. Its large, clean and staffed by friendly, welcoming folks. The equipments are well maintained and many new facilities are here ready for use. I have been regularly attending the PT sessions by Eric and found the sessions are very professional to target on my fitness goals. Well recommended, don‚Äôt hesitate to register here!

author: Christopher Ong
text: Great gym! Spacious and clean! Especially the shower room are one of best of all the outlet I‚Äôve visited. Friendly staff too. Will definitely be back soon really soon.

author: Dhashan Nair Karunakaran
text: Coming here after a year. Many changes and improvements from the last I came. Loving this place as it's big and cozy. More equipments here. Convenient for those working and living around that area. Hope to see this concept and the gym size more at Singapore! Definitely 5/5 for this place!

author: Kang Gerrie
text: AF Pasir Panjang has full range of equipment with ample space. The facilities are clean with adequate sanitiser and tissues for cleaning. The ladies toilet is clean with hair dryer and big mirrors and smells refreshing. It is awesome to train there and they are the best Anything Fitness that i have visited so far.

author: Sarah Tan
text: The gym is very big, with ample space to do workouts and a large variety of workout equipment to try. The staff, Danny and William, are welcoming to newcomers. They showed me around the gym. The gym also has group classes this month.

author: Giulio Baldi
text: Been a member since Nov 2020. The gym is brand new and very spacious, lots of equipments. Being on west coast highway is very easy to reach for me. The staff takes great care of cleaningness and safety measures. If you like functional training is a pretty good place to go.

author: Lyn Khine
text: Great place to workout anytime. I come on weekdays as well as on weekends. Very friendly staff. Thanks!!! üëçüëç ‚Ä¶

author: Go Shaman
text: signed up in 2024 January during their promo.  AF Pasir Panjang made me feel "small" i enjoy that feeling as it means the gym is spacious and not cramped, and i do not feel inhibited during workouts.  the music is soft in the background, staff are attentive and friendly.  equipment selection is varied, they have a pec dec and rear delt machine,   a side lateral raise machine is not available.  shower facility is more than enough for myself, i really like it.  its a extremely easy and shortish walk from Pasir Panjang MRT station. if u are hesitant, reach out to them, they are attentive via WhatsApp.

author: Eric Lau
text: Staffs are helpful and experienced, very wide range of gym equipment as well.

author: oikaru
text: It has been 2 months since I signed up to be a member. Initially, I was skeptical of the reviews as everyone have good things to say. I'm here to make a statement that - YES ANYTIME FITNESS PP IS THAT AMAZING!! from the cleanliness of the toilets to the service of the staff, it feels like a second home to me. One incident that particularly touched my heart was when I had a terrible day but two of the gym staff cheered me up and listened to me. I appreciate the kind gesture of them offering me chocolate too! That aside, the equipment is well maintained and even the gym-goers are kind and friendly. If you're thinking of signing up, PLEASE DO! The Gym Manager William is amazing as well and he bothers to remember which member signs up. Furthermore, AF PP isn't overcrowded with a ton of gym-goers so it feels peaceful and less suffocating gym-ing here :)

author: C Keith
text: Honestly one of the best Anytime Fitness I have ever been too! Huge space, friendly staff, and a variety of equipment. They also make an effort to keep the place clean and tidy. Gym closes from 2pm-3pm to clean, which is not a bother, as most anytime fitness do not offer 24 hours due to COVID. Overall, it is a great gym to workout at!

author: Rex Tan
text: By far the biggest & most spacious AF in Singapore that I ever been. Equipment is quite standard but many squat racks available so no need to queue and there are some special cardio machines that other AF don't have, overall it is a pretty decent gym, good job!

author: Aidah Hafeizi
text: Among all Anytime Fitness I have been this is the best place. The Gym is spacious. The equipment is place in different section like weight training is in one section then cardio is another section. They also have classes which have their own room for classes which is good as it won‚Äôt occupied the gym area. Even though I stay far for now I will still go there to enjoy my gym workout. In future this place will be my most convenient place ever. Lastly the Manager & staffs that I knew mostly very friendly & approachable

author: Chua Jieen
text: Awesome places! Definitely one of the best spots for a workout in Singapore üëçüèº ‚Ä¶

author: Jeremy
text:
Hands down the best Anytime Fitness outlet that I have been to over the years.

The gym is spacious, well equipped and has machines that I couldn‚Äôt find at other outlets. There is also an separate space for classes.

Though it‚Äôs a big gym hygiene has not been sacrificed. Kudos to the team and manager William.

author: Marc JY
text: Really nice AF branch. The facility is spacious, clean, and well stocked with good working and well-maintained equipment and machines. There's also a sizeable shower area and good number of lockers (bring your padlock) so you do not have to worry about washing up pre and post workout, or even about storing your belongings. I manage to briefly speak with the staffs there and they are really friendly and welcoming which is a great touch to the overall experience and visit here. I will definitely recommend this branch to my friends and family when the opportunity arise. Likewise, i do hope i'll find myself opportunities to drop by here more often for sure.

author: Jamie Aeshya
text: AF PP do make you feel comfortable and the music is listenable, the crowd seems friendly, the equipments were in good condition, the space is good, especially the high ceiling. Best of all, William was very helpful  and friendly and hence why I sign up. Prior to this I went to Safra gym at Mount Faber and I did not feel comfortable at all. The reception staff was male and he was not friendly and not helpful or whatsoever at all. Hence this makes me think the difference between William and the Safra MF gym reception. Keep it up!

author: Damia Zeris
text:
The best AF outlet i had been to by far!

Pasir Panjang AF has wide range of equipment, is very spacious and is also a comfortable place to do your workout at with such good music and vibes.

The employees are welcoming and approachable if you need any assistance üëçüèª

Should definitely give it a shot with your next visit as you will not be disappointed

author: bickerbanter
text: Very spacious and clean gym. Very helpful and friendly staff that didn‚Äôt hesitate to go beyond their call of duty! I accidentally spilled my water on the floor and one of the managers was very quick to assist to clean up even though it was my fault. Overall a great experience and definitely others to join!

author: Kumar Dosi
text: Awesome gym. High ceilings, good temperature control, have most of the machines I need, wide array of attachments to go with pulling movements and most importantly, multiple commonly used dumbbells so that one almost never have to wait. And conveniently located on west coast highway.

author: Benedict Heng
text: v helpful staff! spacious with good mix of equipment!

author: x dreamer
text: Visited the gym for the first time, overall great experience. The staff were very friendly and the equipment were all in good condition. It's not crowded with people which is a plus point if you're looking for a quiet gym to workout in. There is also wide variety of classes available for member to sign up.

author: Shawn Kumar
text:
Nice ambience to work on with your friends!!!

Polite and friendly staffs to guide you along the way. New and sophisticated gym equipments to do your workouts.üëç

The place is clean and tidy even when this pandemic period as well.

I feel inspired and motivated whenever I step in to Anytime Fitness Pasir Panjang Branch.

Going to spend most of my days doing my workouts and keeping myself fit in this spectacular environmentüëåüëè

Inspire to be Inspiredüí™Just Do It‚úî

Cheers

~Shawn~

author: Peiwen Yeo
text: Very spacious and big! Equipments are new. My friends and I enjoy coming here. Big and clean toilet. Aircon is of right temperature. it feels like a premium gym.

author: Joan Chua
text:
Jolin is very welcoming with a very cheerful personality who always have a big smile on her face. She did a very good job on touring me around the gym, explaining the gym facilities as well as the gym equipments. When upon having some enquires about the equipments and membership, she is very patience and answer them accordingly!!!
Was very satisfied with her service and please give her a bump on this as well!ü•∞ü•∞

author: Khim Tan
text: Very spacious gym with a wide variety of equipment and classes. I am also genuinely impressed with the standard of customer service at this gym. Even with the current situation (Circuit Breaker), I still have been getting weekly check ins directly from the staff and updates regarding the virtual classes they have organised for the members :)

author: Raag Sudha
text: Really enjoy coming to this gym, the team is very friendly and checks in with me if I don‚Äôt turn up for a week or so which is so good for accountability. Raiyan helped me out with the body scanning machine, so helpful to have stats when on a fat loss journey. Thank you to the team for creating such a positive and laidback environment. My fav gym in SG by far.

author: Rudai Yan
text: Very good gym. The PT Shah is very nice and professional. He gives me a very detailed and informative guide for training, making me become healthier and stronger. Thanks.

author: Elyas Mustasar
text: Amazing gym. Brand new machine. Equipment very well maintained. Trainers and staff are super friendly. Toilet complete with changing room and showers facilities. Have no complaints. Kudos to AF Pasir Panjang.

author: Iskandar
text: One of the best AF. Its spacious, everything is working, clean, and lightly lit up. Have been going past 0200 hours and parking is always available (hourly parking). After gym hungry? Dont worry, theres the famous Fong Seng Nasi Lemak just a minute away.

author: Muhd Saufi Jambari
text: Have been a regular to this gym for years since its near my workplace. Enjoyed the facilities that were well taken care of and nice staff around!

author: Âçéhwaa.
text:
clean and spacious, very nice environment for a good workout. great variety of equipments and well maintained! just started visiting this outlet in the recent months and quite impressed.

one of the better AF outlet, keep up the great vibes and good work!

author: Amanda Lim
text: I actually OWN a (small) gym and I still go to this Anytime location because it has SO MUCH equipment, is never crowded, and is always clean.  Great experience here!

author: Malik M
text:
Fabulous gym, fantastic, friendly staff, clean and spacious bathrooms, a very wide range of exercise equipment, well lighted, good music, state of the art machine to measure the body composition and last but not least - non pushy trainers. The vibe is awesome! A big shoutout to Ms.Dorslina and Mr.Shah for the amazing training sessionüôÇ

Hands down this would be the best Anytime Fitness gym in Singapore. Keep up the good work !

author: first name last name
text: Good gym some equipment can be better

author: Jayme Zhong
text: Huge space with lots of equipment and other amenities (for e.g you can do an evolt active body scan for FREE)! Gym is clean and renovated so everything is nice - and most importantly it‚Äôs spacious!! Feel like most AFs are becoming more and more crowded and cramped so I would recommend this gym 10/10 ‚ò∫Ô∏è

author: Shawn Teo
text:
Risham is the best trainer! As a beginner myself, he has helped me alot with my gym training. He is very knowledgeable in terms of fitness. Highly recommend him if you are looking for a trainer.
The gym is also very spacious and has alot of training facilities. Great place for a workout.

author: Mik Leong
text: Great gym!  One of the biggest AF. Studio for classes is large and spacious. Lots of classes such as Les Mills series and yoga. Instructors and staff are friendly and professional. Location is conveniently located about 2 mins walk from Pasir Panjang MRT.

author: Venka Vimar
text: The Gym Staff including traininers here are friendly, approachable and helpful. The Gym is huge, the biggest I have been to and the equipment are up to date, well maintained. My new favourite AF outlet.

author: Zen
text: The gym is large, spacious and well equipped. Changing rooms and toilets are very well maintained as well. One of the better AF outlets I‚Äôve visited!

author: Andri Kristian
text:
Anytime Fitness is a good and big gym. I enjoyed that there are varieties of equipments there. Though it's definitely on the pricier ends compared to gym at CC or active SG :")

Germaine was my personal trainer while I was there. She helped me to get acquainted with the gym equipments and also many other exercises that trained my whole body. She is knowledgable and patient. Also, she made a list of exercises that I can do myself after the personal training sessions with her ends. Recommended if u have some budget and are beginning ur gym journey üëç

author: ho teckcheong
text: Equipment was clean and tidy, staff was friendly and wide choices of equipment.

author: Freddy Chng
text: Very spacious, super nice staffs that smile and serve, good equipment.

author: Anand prabhu
text: One of the bigger and well kept anytime fitness gym. Great music also regardless the time I am here which helps with the atmosphere. The vending machine also provide a good array of beverages for workout.

author: Maushmi Rawat
text: A good experience at the Gym, the staff is very helpful in explaining each and everything around the gym

author: Wong Say Hai
text: The gym is very spacious and equipments are spreader out fairly. Sufficient machines and free weights to workout too!! The trainers and staff there are very approachable. Enjoyed the AF@Pasir Panjang very much.

author: Dineshwaran Naidu
text: Based on all the anytime fitness I have visited this is the biggest and almost well complete in Singapore.

author: Julian Ang
text:
Editing my review yet again.

Giving credit where it's due. JJ the sr mgr called me after the latest review i gave below. As well as to follow on my request to cancel my anytime fitness membership. He did an excellent job listening and accepting my perspectives whilst maintaining his professionalism on club management policies. Just for that, I'm bumping this place back to 3 stars. Unfortunately, it's too late for me, and I'm not prepared to reconsider my cancelling my membership.
---
The latest iteration of an operations team has frankly taken anal retentive-ness to a whole new level. Instead of actually calling out behaviour that inconveniences clients' use of facilities they call out behaviour and enforce rules that impinge on the EGOs and ultimately selfish dignity of complaining whiners. Extremely hypocritical and terrible leadership. You choose to assuage the egos of whiners over the actual functionality of a gym. Snail trails, coffee cups in corners, syringes in the stalls are ok but someone rolling out his lats with his shirt off, in a corner of the studio away from the main gym floor, coz the shirt gets rolled up as well, is oh-so-wrong. Please get your priorities straight.

The equipment here is fantastic and the gym space too, but you'd think the place is run by staff who simply don't pay attention.

author: ryan seet
text: Spacious, loaded with fresh equipment, friendly staff and patrons. Because of these reasons I started frequent AF Pasir Panjang.  10/10 recommend anyone who‚Äôs reading this review to give it a try, you‚Äôll fall in love with the place.

author: Jonathan Ho
text: Great facilities, and I really enjoy their bodypump and spin classes! Managers and staff are all very helpful and nice as well. Very big, spacious gym, and it's often not that crowded which is nice. :)

author: Yuki Wong
text: The most spacious and awesome gym in Singapore! I feel so comfortable and carefree in this gym as the size of this gym is about 5 or 6 times bigger than most gyms. To top if off, they offer group classes like LesMills BodyPump and BodyCombat which is very motivating to keep one's fitness on track. Additionally, they have super clean and abundant shower rooms with Rainshower amenities which makes showering after workouts a luxurious experience. The gym manager, i think his name is William, is very attentive and dedicated to helping the gym members. I will definitely recommend this AF gym outlet to anyone who is considering to sign up for a gym membership üëçüëçüëçüëçüëç

author: Jia Xin Lim
text: Went there my first time and was impressed on how large and spacious it is. The facilities and equipment are also well-maintained. Will definitely come back to this gym again.

author: Brad Bowyer
text: Been only 6 weeks but I am well on my way to my fitness goals... Thanks to Nikman for the training, Thiban and Shah for the support and great service... A great gym with knowledgeable staff... Highly recommended

author: Wight G
text:
Sometimes, they're open anytime, but if you want to come anytime, be disappointed because you can only do that sometimes. They should change their name to Sometimes Open Fitness.

Area is large, facilities are clean, but opening hours are limited. I don't advise signing on with this gym if you want to come at the quiet hours. They're closed. If you come during office hours / after work, then it's OK. I do regret coming here.

Oh and the reviews? All those 5 stars? The gym will pester you and WhatsApp you to get you to give them 5 stars. For that, I'm removing another star to 2.

author: Jian Che
text: Germaine is great! So helpful with the registration and so prompt with enquiries on social media! Efficient and clean gym, one of the best af gyms in sg! Strongly recommended!

author: Pia Nieminen
text: Nice, calm, clean and functional gym. Staff very friendly and helpful. Everything works, and always nice to come here :)

author: Aaron Ritchie
text:
I've just moved into the Pasir Panjang area and I am quite happy that Anytime Fitness Pasir Panjang is my new local gym. When I walked in on my first session, I was greeted by the friendly William who recognised I was new to this particular club. He offered by a guided tour of all the facilities to put me at ease and know where everything is.

The facilities are plentiful and spacious. There are three distinct areas to the gym; a cardio machine section, a padded class studio, and an expansive free weights room. The weights room has four squat racks, and plenty of weights to go around, as well as two rowing machines and two air bikes if you're looking to throw some cardio into your weights routine. The padded class studio is a great place to go and work on your core or do some stretches in a quiet environment (when there's no classes happening).

The gym is located just a short walk down from Pasir Panjang MRT station on the Circle Line.

author: Monica Marcellina
text: Like many said, biggest AF gym in SG. Many treadmills available, various range of equipment and free weights! Not crowded but I went on saturday evening. Spacious changing room and many lockers, which not many AFs branches provide. Sadly, not my home gym but I will return üëçüèª ‚Ä¶

author: Fauzi Stoner
text: Loving the isolated location away from residential estate. Staff are excellent and friendly, the gym is huge. But could use more equipment,cables,plates even dumbell with all those spaces. More mirrors would be great as well. Other then that keep up the good work!!

author: Eugene K
text:
I must say, this gym is not just spacious, but also well-equipped with a vast studio, a free weights area, and a machine area. You can find 6 squat racks, 2 cable machines, and 1 smith machine, which are all in excellent condition.

While the gym sees a manageable crowd during the morning and lunchtime, it can get a bit crowded during dinner time and night. However, it doesn't really affect the overall gym experience.

One thing that really stood out for me is the Evolt body analyzer, which has been immensely helpful in evaluating my body composition. It enables me and my physical trainer to keep a check on my body fat and muscle composition, leading to progress monitoring.

Speaking of my physical trainer, Risham, I must say he is exceptional. With his vast experience, he has been able to guide me in proper movements for both free weights and machines. Besides, I have learned many useful stretching techniques from him, which have helped me improve my flexibility.

What's more impressive is that Risham has also taught me additional exercise techniques such as sport massage and suspension training. He focuses on compound movements that stress multiple muscle groups and has helped me cover the whole body effectively.

In short, if you are looking for a gym with excellent equipment and an experienced physical trainer like Risham, this is the place to be.

author: harith rahim
text: This particular branch is totally different from other AF outlets i have been to. Staff is very well informed and attentive to each person. Very clean and sanitary and I see them de sanitise equipments at various timings, even when I came in a 2am once. Very professional service, looks like I found my favourite outlet now!

author: Syahirah Halim
text: I popped by after class at NUS one afternoon (around 4-5pm) and it was amazing. Not a huge crowd yet but I was shocked by the space and facilities. Prolly one of the better AF gyms out there. Will try to work out here more often if I have the chance! Service was friendly too!

author: adam saifullah
text: Staff is really friendly and the members here are also chill and friendly...especially claire ,very kind staff

author: Winston Jun
text:
What can i say, Anytime Fitness Pasir Panjang has everything that you want in a local gym. First off, the equipment are well mantained and clean and in these times of Covid, you see disinfectant sprays and wipes at almost every machine! No joke, its like every corner you turn, you would see 2 or 3 bottles. On top of that the space and equipment available is in ABUNDANCE i tell you, and to add on to that, they recently added even more equipement! You would find everything you need here.
The toilets, so clean and well mantained! They have a white colour scheme that is in no danger of getting stained or dirty despite it being a gym. This is thier commitment to hygiene and cleanliness. You have adequate number of shower rooms and changing rooms. They even have an aircon inside the toilet to keep you cool after your hot shower!

But the greatest thing for me, is the friendliness and warmth of the staff. They greet you so warmly like family at the door. So much so that if you walked in drenched from the rain, their hospitatlity would keep you warm. But please be advised to change out of your wet clothes. Among all the Anytime Fitness outlets i have been to, this one give me the most welcoming experience. There was once their club manger , William changed the weights for me on the bench press as he was worried that i was using different kind of weight plates, what a guy!

All in all, if you are looking for a place to start off your fitness journey, look no futher than Anytime Fitness Pasir Panjang! You won't regret it.

author: Yuri Fedoseev
text:
A big clean gym. There‚Äôre a lot of racks for squats or bench pressing.
The only issue is loud music during group classes. I‚Äôve stopped visiting the gym because of it. Can‚Äôt understand how 5-6 people survive with this sound level

author: Michael Jason
text:
Very friendly staff, very clean, highly professional in their approach. Gym is kept tip top. Ample amount of space and equipment.

Special note to William for being friendly and welcoming to the place.

author: Johnathan Tan
text: Have been to multiple AF outlets, and the Pasir Panjang outlet is spacious, well equipped for all muscle groups. Clean and staff are friendly too. Have actually been training here more than the outlet I initially signed with!

author: Vicki Lyana Dhillon
text: I have been working out here for almost a year a year here. The gym is spacious and we'll taken care of. The gym has great equipments and friendly staff. Friendly environment.

author: Leo Mrc
text:
Anytime Fitness had the brilliant idea of creating a scheme to charge extra money to customers in a legal way. The gym chain has appointed a third party to collect the monthly fee and when the partner does not carry on the transaction they charge 14 dollars to customers.

Aggressive behavior to customers just to make extra revenue is completely uncorrelated to my personal values.
Please reading this review just realize the bad faith of the gym trying JUST ONE TIME to take your monthly fee and IMMEDITATELY CHARGING 14 dollars for not succeeding.

the business model of AF says it all about how you treat customers

author: Khin Thuzar Naing (Justina)
text:
I accidentally left my work mobile phone in the female changing room after working out...
I only realized it next morning and got really worried as it contained important information..
I contacted the gym immediately. The person in charge on duty returned my call in 15 mins time.
He was quite professional and did the necessary verification then asked me to come down and collect it from him..
I was really thankful to the honest gym janitor and gym management team..
Additionally, I would rate this club for 5 stars for the cleanliness, spacious, equipment maintenance and friendly staffs..
Please keep it up..

author: Nick Ng
text: One of, if not the biggest anytime fitness gym in Singapore!!! Equipment and toilet are all very clean and well maintained. Staff are very friendly whom would say hi to you!

author: Wacleus Chin
text: The gym is considered quite spacious, however, with the SMM guideline there are not many slots available for the class. It's quite 'challenging' to secure a slot sometimes. Equipment are good. The gym manager William is very helpful and responsive to my enquiries. One suggestion is to stick with the old schedule for the body pump class during weekend (9am is really quite early haha).

author: Bay Yong Sheng
text: Very well equipped gym with almost all the equipments needed for Indoor cardio, resistance Training and even Caliestnic. There is a very big space for schedule lessons and activities, toilet are really clean too. And The dude call William is a pretty fun guy to talk to. That is why i rate 5 star. But What can be better is if they provide toilet for bathing will be excellent.

author: Judith Quinzon

text: Although i‚Äôm a member of the outlet in Admiralty, Woodlands, and having been to all 4 outlets in Woodlands, Potong Pasir, and Boon Keng, the Pasir Panjang outlet is by far the best. The pros outweigh the con of having to travel to Pasir Panjang all the way from Woodlands. The place is big, spacious, with plenty of equipment. I mostly workout after midnight and it‚Äôs totally empty. author: Janie S.B Tan
text:
Everyone would have read about how big and spacious and new the gym is so I wouldn't repeat the same comments again. I would like to comment on the customer service aspect of it and I must say as of now, I'm blown away by it, be it the instructors or administrators.

I used to be a gym member for many years before California fitness closed down. After ten years of not being in the gym, signing up for one somehow felt a bit scary for me, but from sign-up to registering for classes to attending classes, it has been a really pleasant experience for me. Sign-up was easy and relaxing because the staff was really friendly (Alex and William); Class registration is really quick using the app and the instructors, though having to teach very very small classes because afterall this is a new gym, are very friendly, full of energy and enthusiastic nonetheless.

When the COVID hit, I was worried about my gym membership because the gym is close to my workplace but very far from my home, but the team reacted very fast and William the club manager suspended my membership. I am very grateful and surprised by their understanding because in my former gym, when I had to be overseas for a few months and I asked for a suspension, it was a real struggle to get it approved.

And during this COVID period, I get messages from the gym sometimes on various things like free online workout classes by their instructors, free temporary access to Les milles classes, or just simply a hi and check on my well-being.

And though it is not directly affecting me per se, I love the fact that they are still paying their staff even though I know most gyms have asked their staff to go on unpaid leave due to the COVID situation. I always believe that happy employees means happy customers. I really have to give them my thumbs and toes up for this.

Their passion to provide world class service and utmost care for their gym members and staff really makes me proud to be part of the AF Pasir Panjang family.

Good job AF PP.
